value.0: Hello there *grins at you giving you the sense that you might just get robbed*
Ahh the other clans... which would you care to know about.
Bow if you have to, scrape if you must, and slit their throats for the blood.
There are some real impurities in these bitches' blood. I say Caine took a shine to a monster some time ago, and the Tzimisce are the result.
Our fellow sorcerers, conjuring up solid results to our shadows. Of course, they haven't half the edge we do - I'd be more afraid of my cousin's ghost-fire than the clumsy pyrotechnics of a Warlock.
Their eyes and ears are just too damn sharp for their own good. Be a shame if something happened to those catacomb crawlers.
They see too damn much and don't buy into anybody's delusions but their own. Don't like them, not one bit.
They look pretty soft, but these are some hard bastards, that's for sure. They ain't the new kid on the block, and they don't play kid games. *shrug* You gotta respect that.

Our poor cousins, if that's possible. They dig themselves holes in the mud and drag their matted asses into the city only when someone whistles 'em up. Lapdogs gone feral, and who needs that kind of pet?

What is everyone so afraid of? Even a deal with the Devil isn't so bad if you read the fine print. Snakes can't poison me, and I don't have a soul to lose. Then again, if everyone thought the same as me, I wouldn't have "preferred custom" status. So let 'em cringe.
Poet shirts, wine and roses, leather jackets, artsy tattoos, Kill me if I ever start acting like one of those limpdicks.
Go ahead and let them rattle their cages. If they bend the bars, we'll follow them out - and if the zookeeper shows up, they're the first to go.
The only good thing about them is that the other clans hate and fear them so much that you can easily get plenty of cold bodies between yourself and one of these devourers.

We normally trust nobody, not even our own clan mates, but work together when necessary to bilk, rob or topple an outsider enemy. Often grandiose pledges of family loyalty are made to one another, although neither party expects very much to come of the vows.

As Ravnos we have indulged in our particular vices so long that we have become addicted to them. Each Ravnos has a weakness for some form of trickery, deceit or mischief, weather it be gambling, lying, theft, blackmail or even cleverly framed murder. When the opportunity to indulge presents itself, we must be very cautious or succumb to our compulsion. The longer the Ravnos is exposed to the possibility using our vice, the harder it is for us to resist. If there is nothing opposing the action, then we cannot resist.
We are nomadic vampires who Embrace few childer. However, we are fairly indiscriminate in siring childer.

Celerity is a Discipline that grants vampires supernatural speed and finesse by expending vitae. Presence, the discipline of unnatural attraction and emotional control. This discipline is the ultimate exaltation of the "Power of personality" that many kindred have.Potence is Discipline that grants the vampires supernatural strength.
We are nomadic by nature; we all feel the wanderlust upon us from time to time. Members of the clan often travel taking shelter wherever we may. .
